Zamfara State Government is to benefit from Federal Government
partnership for expanded water supply, sanitation and hygiene programme, as contract for the construction of 32 new simple solar borehole in three Local Government Areas of the State. State Commissioner for Rural Development and Cooperatives, Alhaji
Abubakar Abdullahi, who disclosed this at the formal flag off of the
project, said the beneficial Local Government Areas are, Kaura Namoda,
Bungudu and Maradun. He further said, under the programme 18 conventional boreholes would be rehabilitated and upgraded to solar borehole. The commissioner however, said another 60 broken-down hand pumps at
the three selected local government areas would be rehabilitated by
the federal government. According to him, another set of three local government areas-Anka,
Zurmi and Bukkuyum would also benefit from Partnership Expanded Water
Supply, Sanitation and Hygiene Programme (PEWASH). “The PEWASH programme is going to be implemented in six select local
government areas of Anka, Bungudu, Bukkuyum, Maradun, Kaura Namoda and
Zurmi”, he added. In his speech, Programme Manager RUWATSAN, Sani Gurbin-Bore, said the
agency and federal ministry for water resources have been working
together to create a better living condition for Rural dwellers with
focus on access to safety water and sanitation. According to him, the main objective of PEWASH was to prioritize the
achievement of 100% access to water supply and improved sanitation by
the year 2030.